text:
I choose to learn information-communication this year because before, I wanted to be a journalist. But now, we are in december, and I know now that I don't want to be a journalist. In fact, I want now to be a planner (and not just a wedding-planner). Speaking english is very important, in this licence and more in this job. Sometime we have to talk with other people, and everyone speak english. I choose this licence and this university because we can go in an other country, learn and work with people in the Paris... Most of my friends want to be journalist, they want to work at the TV, on the radio... But I think that the licence Information-Communication can be benefic for everyone: We learn to speak, to argument, and most important, we laern to use carefully social networks. Why ? Because social networks are now a tool to work.
I want to be a planner because I love to organize some event. Since I am in Paris, I organized a lot of events for association (like Ride Like Share), but thanks to my studies, I do also the communication around events (on social network, making post, but also poster, flyeurs...). Making event, step by step is now my favorite activity. More, with this job, you make your friend, familly, and people happy.
As I said, before I wanted to be a journalist, since I was a child. I always saw journalist on the TV, but also in my familly. Making interview, meet famous people... but I think it is a very hard job today, in our society. Journalists want to inform the world of the news but sometime it is dangerous. For example, today in Paris, or in Paris, or in Paris, a lots of journalists were killed just because they were here, just because they were doing their job. But we need journalist, without, how can we know what happend ? So for that, I am happy that my friends want to be journalist.
 This webpage performs keylogging of input into a textbox. In other words, when focused on the textbox below, the page will record each time you hit a key or select text with your mouse. All of the data is stored locally on your machine in the DOM and is downloadable as a JSON file. More information about the motivation of this project and the format of the produced data are available here.
